			    <div class="fragment" style="font-size:150%">"Veterinarians?"</div>
			    </div>
			  </section>

			  <section>
			    <p>
			      Equine and human larynges are similar. Our veterinarian friends have access to interesting image data and physiological measurements.
			    </p>
			    <br>
			    <div class="fragment">
			    <button onclick="changeImage(3)">
			      <img id="image3" src="assets/man_horse.png">
			    </button>
			    </div>
			  </section>

			  <section>
			    <section>
			      <h3>The approach</h3>
			      <div class="fragment">
			      <ul>
				<li>DOMAIN: obtain a realistic 3D geometry </li>
				<li>PHYSICS: Navier-Stokes, fluid-structure interaction, turbulence</li>
				<li>MESH: design appropriate mesh </li>
				<li>SOLVE: use suitable numerical methods </li>
				<li>VALIDATE: Compare with lab measurements (e.g. pressure)</li>
				<li class="fragment"><b>Iterate</b></li>
			      </ul><br>
			      <div class="fragment">
				<img width="45%" src="http://math.nie.edu.sg/kcang/TME_paper/ang1.gif">
			      </div>
			      </div>
			    </section>
			  </section>


